2. TreeMapEmployeeSalaryUpdate
Easy
100 points
• 125 min suggested
Problem Description
1) Write a java program to create an object of TreeMap<String, Float> class, add five employees details(names & salaries),
iterate employees details by using ListIterator interface to add 5000.00 bonus salary to every employee & display latest data. 
Note: Use Map.Entry to extract the data while iterating.

Examples
Example 1
Input:
John 30000
Ravi 28000
Meera 35000
Asha 27000
Kiran 40000
Output:
Updated Employee Details (After Bonus):
Name: Asha, Salary: 32000.0
Name: John, Salary: 35000.0
Name: Kiran, Salary: 45000.0
Name: Meera, Salary: 40000.0
Name: Ravi, Salary: 33000.0



import java.util.*;
public class Test{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        TreeMap<String,Double> emp = new TreeMap<>();
/*
        emp.put("John",30000f);
        emp.put("Ravi",28000f);
        emp.put("Meera",35000f);
        emp.put("Asha",27000f);
        emp.put("Kiran",40000f);

        */

        for(int i=0; i<5; i++){
            String name = IO.readln();
            double salary = Double.parseDouble(IO.readln());
            emp.put(name,salary);
        }

        IO.println("Updated Employee Details (After Bonus):");
        emp.forEach((k,v) -> IO.println("Name: "+k+", Salary: "+(v+5000)));

    }
}



